Sentencas: A novel cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-delta (SBF) oxide is synthesized and evaluated as cathode for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-δ as a novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The chemical compatibility, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion coefficient and electrochemical performance are investigated.
Titulo: Cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-δ as a novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SBF exhibits a good chemical compatibility with the La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte at 1000 degrees C for 5 h. Its electrical conductivity is 9.2-11.8 S cm(-1) over the temperature range of 600-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-δ as a novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC of SBF is 17.2 x 10(-6) K-1 between 30 degrees C and 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-δ as a novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistances of the SBF cathode on LSGM are 0.075 Omega cm(2) and 0.117 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-δ as a novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Maximum power density is as high as 417 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C based on a 300 mu m thick LSGM electrolyte.
Titulo: Cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-δ as a novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Preliminary results imply that SBF is an excellent oxygen reduction electrode candidate for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Cobalt-free quintuple perovskite Sm1.875Ba3.125Fe5O15-δ as a novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
